Nato is assessing a request from the alliance's military authorities to send a few thousand more troops to Afghanistan. WASHINGTON - Nato is assessing a request from the alliance's military authorities to send a few thousand more troops to Afghanistan and will make a decision on the scale and scope of the mission within weeks, Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg said in London on Wednesday.&quot;We are now assessing that request. We will make decisions on the scale and scope of the mission within weeks but this is not about returning back to a combat operation in Afghanistan,&quot; he said after meeting British Prime Minister Theresa May at her office.&quot;It will continue to be a train, assist and advise operation,&quot; he added.